{
  "stem": "24163.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it became more noticeable in the school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first thing the teachers did-- the first thing that happened-- some of the teachers, especially some that I liked, particularly, were dismissed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were members of the Catholic party.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were members of the Social Democratic Party.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were simply dismissed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were-- they appointed teachers who were outright Nazis.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember one, especially, was our music teacher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had an excellent music teacher, but he was thrown out of school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the fellow who was in charge of the stormtroopers band, you know, the guy that marches in front with the baton, he, all of a sudden, became our music teacher.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he was a vicious anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in his classroom, it started where he immediately separated all the Jewish students-- there were 11 of us in that class-- he separated us from all the other students.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had to sit in the back of the classroom, and the Gentiles in front.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He never called on us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He never taught us anything, except called us names.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when-- when it came time for a report card, he failed each and every one of us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Even so one of my friends was a good piano player, it didn't make any difference.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We all failed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So-- but that kind of separation between the Jewish and the Gentile students then also happened in the other classrooms.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we could tell, from one month to the next, that it became more and more difficult for us Jewish students to attend classes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And many, many of them dropped out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I think I was among the last three or four who stayed in school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were only boys.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The girls went to something called [GERMAN], which is a girl's high school.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
